Statistical model calculations.
For calculating the ratios, the Sigma-m+Sigma-g values
reported earlier were used. See REL-REF
The Julich compact cyclotron CV-28 .
In present work the activity of Co-58-m was
determined via X-Ray spectrometry and via the activity
of the ground state Co-58-g which was measured as a
function of time via standard gamma-ray spectrometry.
From an analysis of the growth and decay curve of
Co-58-g it is possible to obtain the initial activities
of both Co-58-m and Co-58-g.  This method was found to
be suitable when the activity of Co-58-m was relativity
high.
The count rates were corrected for random pileup losses
as well as for gamma-ray or X-ray abundance and the
efficiency of the detector.  Correction for coincidence
loss was also taken into account.
The X-Ray spectrometric studies were performed
using either Si(Li) or an intrinsic HPGe detector with
Be window.
the total error in each cross section was
obtained by combining the individual errors in
quadrature.
the error in the beam current
